Title: tldr_13
Description: This projects aims to use crowdsourcing to summarize long, verbose texts. You will help us by selecting the most important sentences from a short block of text.
Answer.feedback: LOL I think it's funny how your instructions were the longest when your group is tl;dr I think this is an interesting idea, but it was pretty hard to just choose sentences I found most important, but I see that's just due to the task. It may be interesting to ask the inverse question -- to remove the sentences that aren't so important. I think a valid compensation would be $0.10.
